          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is a data swamp?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A data swamp is a data lake without governance — nobody knows what data is in it, where it came from, or whether it is trustworthy. It becomes unusable. Prevention requires cataloging, metadata, and clear ownership from day one.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Where do data lakes physically live?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Most modern data lakes sit on cloud object storage: Amazon S3, Azure Data Lake Storage (ADLS), or Google Cloud Storage. Compute layers like Databricks, Spark, or Snowflake read the data in place without moving it.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
